    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-02T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-02T12:00:00-05:00" n="386"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">102.1/9601a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-02T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 2, 1943—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1731. From the Secretary of the Treasury for Adler.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Ambassador Wei has informed the Treasury that prices in China are no
                        longer rising but, because of gold sales, have in fact begun to
                        decline.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Telegraph reply of your views and comments on this matter is requested by
                        Treasury. [Morgenthau.]</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
